# Backdrop

A backdrop is used as a layer that visually helps separate background elements from a featured foreground component, like a modal.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/backdrop
```

```tsx
import { Backdrop } from '@ids-ts/backdrop';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `light` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `open` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `zIndex` | `number` | No | The value for the Backdrop's z-index |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface BackdropProps extends ThemeableElement<'div'> {
  /**
   * Determines the background color of the backdrop
   *
   * @default false
   */
  light?: boolean;
  /**
   * Determines whether to load the backdrop or not
   *
   * @default false
   */
  open?: boolean;
  /** The value for the Backdrop's z-index */
  zIndex?: number;
}
```

</details>

